@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
    var errorMessage = TempData["ErrorMessage"] as string;
}

@if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(errorMessage))
{
    <div class="alert alert-danger">
        @errorMessage
    </div>
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/site.css" />
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f0f8ff; /* Light blue background */
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        ul {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding: 0;
            list-style: none;
        }
        ul li {
            background: #e6f7ff; /* Light cyan background */
            margin: 5px 0;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .example {
            background: #f9f9f9;
            padding: 10px;
            border-left: 5px solid #007bff;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .example pre {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 10px;
            background: #e2e2e2;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to the Roleplaying Campaign Manager</h1>
        <p>Welcome to the Roleplaying Campaign Manager website where you can manage, customize and log your group's role-playing campaigns.</p>
        <p>Ideal for handling role-playing system rules, handling your own house rules, or managing custom non-rule-based notes for campaign logging.</p>
        <p>We have efficient navigation between Notes.</p>
        <p>Choose between pre-provided templates, note types, and generators to create and customize your notes. Or create your own template, note types, or generators.</p>

        <h2>How to Start:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Register and/or Login</li>
            <li>Create a Campaign</li>
            <li>Invite Players with appropriate roles</li>
            <li>Create Sessions for the Campaign</li>
            <li>Before, during, or after the game session create or add Notes</li>
            <li>Read your notes during a game session to always be up to date with your game master plans. Use built-in Scripts (Generators) to modify the content of Notes which influences your campaign's state.</li>
            <li>Read notes after a game session to refresh your memory about important data. Notes can describe any rulebook-based or non-rulebook-based data.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Important things to remember:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>The Note's Content must be a valid JSON string.</li>
            <li>The generator script (content) must be written in C# and must return a string, which is assigned to the Note's (JSON) content, so must be a JSON string as well. Therefore the genrator's script is for JSON string and variable procesing</li>
            <li>The Note's format is determined by the template, the Note's NoteType uses. To inject the Note's JSON data into a Template use the "<---(.*?)--->" regular expression where (.*?) can be any word.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="example">
            <h3>Example:</h3>
            <p>Given the JSON string:</p>
            <pre>
{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "position": "Software Engineer",
    "status": "approved",
    "company": "Tech Solutions"
}
            </pre>
            <p>And the following Template:</p>
            <pre>
Hello, <---name--->!

We are pleased to inform you that your application for the position of <---position---> has been <---status--->.

Best regards,
<---company---> Team
            </pre>
            <p>The result will be:</p>
            <pre>
Hello, John Doe!

We are pleased to inform you that your application for the position of Software Engineer has been approved.

Best regards,
Tech Solutions Team
            </pre>
        </div>

        <ul>
            <li>The Generators for a Note have a run date in the campaigns. If a Campaign's game date changes and passes a generator's run date, then the system tries to compile and execute the generator's script.</li>
            <li>If you have any further questions please write to adamhuszar24@gmail.com</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
